radiographic_examinations.findings: The stomach remains moderately distended with air and ingested material. There are no abnormally dilated loops of large or small bowel. Moderate stool burden and residual enteric contrast is noted throughout the colon. There is no free intraperitoneal air. Osseous structures are unremarkable. There is atelectasis at the lung bases. There are no unexplained soft tissue calcifications or radiopaque foreign bodies.
